<header>Inline vs. Inline Blocks</header>

<section>
	<article>
		<h3>Inline vs. Inline Blocks</h3>
		<h4>06/15/14</h4>
		
		<p>Text here </p>

		<div class="demonstration"

		Inline elements are meant to span horizontally
		Respect left and right margins and padding, but do not respect top & bottom margins and padding 
		Cannot have width and height set
		Other elements can sit to left and right

		Block elements are meant to stack vertically
		Respect all margins and padding
		Force a line break after element

		Inline-blocks combine these two others
		Respect all margins and padding
		Width and height can be set
		Other elements can sit to left and right


		Initial display of same text in boxes for these three

		Show what happens when margins and padding specified

		Show what happens when height, width specified



	</article>
</section>

